quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  25,44,"Do you suppose that most of them listen or exercise their reason? They are just like cattle; indeed, they are further astray from the way"
  25,45,Have you not regarded how your Lord spreads the twilight? (Had He wished He would have made it stand still.) Then We made the sun a beacon for it
  25,46,"Then We retract it toward Ourselves, with a gentle retracting"
  25,47,It is He who made for you the night as a covering and sleep for rest and He made the day a recall to life
  25,48,"And it is He who sends the winds as harbingers of His mercy, and We send down from the sky purifying water"
  25,49,with which We revive a dead country and provide water to many of the cattle and humans We have created
  25,50,Certainly We distribute it among them so that they may take admonition. But most people are only intent on ingratitude
  25,51,"Had We wished, We would have sent a warner to every town"
  25,52,"So do not obey the faithless, but wage a great jihad against them with it"
  25,53,"It is He who merged the two seas: this one sweet and agreeable, and that one briny and bitter, and between the two He set a barrier and a forbidding hindrance"
  25,54,"It is He who created the human being from water, then invested him with ties of blood and marriage, and your Lord is all-powerful"
  25,55,"They worship besides Allah that which neither brings them any benefit nor causes them any harm, and the faithless one is ever an abettor against his Lord"